				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You can &quot;cheat&quot; your way around HW sprite limitations if you DMA data to OAM during HBlank, however, this is more easily done on the GBC rather than the original DMG, since double speed mode allows you to calculate anything you want in half the normal time, and HDMA are really handy without manually having to call the old OAM DMA via an interrupt in HBlank. You'll still have 10 per scanline, but I've one GBC demo with (it claims) 100 sprites or some such.</div>

